race.comment: POBLANO (6) went around at big odds on debut last start, and finished a solid second, only a neck away from the winner over 1200m at Ascot. William Pike picks up the ride, and she can go one better. DIAMOND CHOUX (5) resumed a fortnight ago and finished seventh, after getting a long way back early on over 1200m at Ascot. She's a likely improver second up, and can figure in the top 3 this time. GINGER TED (2) is a 7-start maiden who finished well back in a stronger field last time out over 1400m at Ascot after giving away a big start. Expect better in an easier field this time. JUST RICH LIKA (1) has missed the placings in his last two runs, but is better than that, and from a decent draw, he can bounce back into form in a modest field like this. BY THE WOOD (11) finished fourth fresh up here nearly 3 weeks ago, and won't have to improve by much to be a top three hope here.
